<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3755] ij&apos;s help text lacks the optional [HOLD | NOHOLD] syntax for GET CURSOR</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3755</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ij&apos;s help command shows the syntax of GET CURSOR as:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;GET &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;SCROLL INSENSITIVE&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; CURSOR name AS &apos;SQL-J query&apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
                               &amp;#8211; gets a cursor (JDBC result set) on the query&lt;br/&gt;
                               &amp;#8211; SCROLL cursors are only available &lt;br/&gt;
                               &amp;#8211; in JDBC 2.0 and higher. &lt;br/&gt;
                               &amp;#8211; (Cursor scroll type is ignored in JDBC 1.X.) &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One can actually also specify holdability, so the syntax show read:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;GET &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;SCROLL INSENSITIVE&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;HOLD | NOHOLD&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; CURSOR name AS &apos;SQL-J query&apos;;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and the comment should also state that HOLD is the default.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12399542">DERBY-3755</key>
